com.taliter.fiscal.device

Interface FiscalPacket

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractFiscalPacket, HasarFiscalPacket

    public interface FiscalPacket
extends java.io.Serializable
    A request to or response from a fiscal device. A packet is a vector of byte arrays called fields. Fields cannot be null. Fields are accessed using a zero-based index up to getSize() - 1. All operations that set values of fields may grow the size of the vector as needed, adding empty fields if necessary.
